{
  "stem": "10587.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, this-- when they find that we are here, hiding, they will throw in one or two grenades and kill everyone there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, and I don't want to die this way, I told him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we were-- and so we-- one evening at-- when it got-- when became dark, we walked from [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Shodula ?]-- my father, myself, and my younger brother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he must have-- my father must have gotten some maps to, to realize which way to, to go to another camp, another ghetto, which was from Bielsko, not far from Sosnowiec.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We walked-- excuse me-- we walked all night and through the fields, through the cornfields, and through-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] off the beaten path.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And off, off-- so, so there's no roads.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And no one could-- and we came there, dead tired, to this place outside of Bielsko thatt was also a, a ghetto, and where my aunt and uncle and, and, and also the youngest brother, and, and, and, and two brothers.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One was-- one's name is Jack Rosenbaum, who is still alive, his brother, Shemek, who was about the same age as my brother and, and my aunt and uncle.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they dug a hole in, in-- outside, in a, in a storage bin.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, and they put a mattress down in the hole.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they also put wood on top of it, you know, and so that the Germans couldn't-- and so when we came there, was no room for us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was like a-- real like a grave, that they slept in, enough room for, you know, sideways to lie, for four people.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we couldn't get down there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were hiding in the same storage bin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a lot of wood, firewood.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
